      <p>
        The Mirka&reg; DEOS II Delta 663X (model MID6634044US) is a compact, direct-electric
        delta-shaped orbital sander with a 100 &times; 152 &times; 152 mm (4" &times; 6" &times; 6")
        triangular backing pad and a 3 mm orbit. The triangular pad makes it suited to corners,
        profiles, edges, vertical surfaces, and hard-to-reach areas. This page covers the US/Canada
        (110&ndash;120 V) English content of the combined DEOS II operating instructions, which
        document the 343X, 353X, 383X, and 663X models together; specifications and parts below are
        called out for the <strong>663X</strong> specifically.
      </p>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/mirka-deos-663x/p03_00.png" alt="Top view of the Mirka DEOS II control panel showing the On/Off button, LED bar, speed plus and minus buttons, and the 3.0 mm orbit lever" />
        <figcaption>Figure 1 &mdash; Top-panel controls: On/Off key, LED bar, Speed+ / Speed&minus; buttons, and the variable-speed lever (marked 3.0 for the 3 mm orbit)</figcaption>
      </div>

