      <h2>Getting Started</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>When unpacking, make sure the tool is intact, complete, and undamaged in transport. Never use a damaged tool.</li>
        <li>Check that the delta backing pad is correctly attached and tightened.</li>
        <li>Connect the power cord to the tool, then to a grounded outlet (110 VAC, 50&ndash;60 Hz).</li>
        <li>For maximum performance, use the tool with a Mirka dust extractor (or other suitable unit) and Mirka net sanding products. Connecting the tool's power cord to the dust extractor's outlet enables the extractor's autostart function.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Operation</h2>
      <ol>
        <li>The tool is intended to be used hand-held and can be operated in any position. <strong>Note:</strong> the sander can develop a torque reaction when started &mdash; keep a firm grip and footing.</li>
        <li>Make sure the sander is switched off. Select a suitable abrasive and secure it centered on the backing pad. For best results, use a Mirka backing pad with a Mirka net sanding product.</li>
        <li>Switch on the sander by pressing the On/Off key. The Multi-purpose LED flashes green.</li>
        <li>Press the lever to start sanding.</li>
        <li>Adjust speed between 5,000 RPM and the set maximum by changing the lever position.</li>
        <li>Always place the tool on the work surface <strong>before</strong> starting it, and remove it from the surface <strong>before</strong> stopping it.</li>
        <li>When finished, press the On/Off key to turn off. All LEDs turn off except the wireless indication LED if the tool is connected.</li>
      </ol>

      <h3>Speed Settings</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Adjusting max RPM:</strong> Press <strong>Speed+</strong> or <strong>Speed&minus;</strong> to set the maximum. Steps are 5,000, 6,000, 7,000, 7,500, 8,000, 9,000, and 10,000 RPM.</li>
        <li><strong>Variable mode (default):</strong> Speed varies linearly with lever position.</li>
        <li><strong>Fixed mode:</strong> Speed stays at the set maximum whenever the tool runs.</li>
        <li><strong>Toggle modes:</strong> Press <strong>Speed+</strong> and <strong>Speed&minus;</strong> simultaneously to switch between variable and fixed modes.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Bluetooth</h3>
      <p>The DEOS II is equipped with Bluetooth Low Energy and can connect to the MyMirka app for additional functionality (RF: 2402&ndash;2480 MHz, 8 dBm EIRP).</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Connect the power cord to a mains outlet.</li>
        <li>Press and hold the <strong>Speed+</strong> button while switching the tool on with the On/Off button.</li>
        <li>The wireless indication LED blinks blue to show Bluetooth is active; it turns solid when a connection is established.</li>
        <li>Bluetooth is deactivated when the tool is disconnected from the mains outlet.</li>
      </ol>
      <div class="note">
        If the MyMirka app is not installed or is not available in your country, do not activate Bluetooth.
      </div>

      <h2>Maintenance</h2>

      <div class="danger">
        <strong>Always disconnect power before maintenance.</strong> Only use original Mirka spare parts.
        Repairs by a non-authorized repairer will breach the Mirka warranty.
      </div>

      <h3>Replacing the Backing Pad</h3>
      <p>On the 663X the pad is held by eight screws &mdash; four 4 &times; 8 mm and four 4 &times; 16 mm (no 8 mm screws; those apply only to the 70 &times; 198 mm 383X pad).</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Turn the tool upside down.</li>
        <li>Remove the four 4 &times; 8 mm screws.</li>
        <li>Remove the four 4 &times; 16 mm screws.</li>
        <li>Remove the backing pad.</li>
        <li>Fit the new pad, then fit the 4 &times; 16 mm screws followed by the 4 &times; 8 mm screws.</li>
        <li>Finally, tighten all screws to 2.4 Nm (1.8 ft-lb).</li>
      </ol>

      <div class="figure">
        <img src="/manuals/mirka-deos-663x/p16_01.png" alt="Underside diagram of the DEOS II showing the screw positions A and B that hold the delta backing pad to the backing plate" />
        <figcaption>Figure 2 &mdash; Backing pad screw locations (A and B) on the underside of the sander</figcaption>
      </div>

      <div class="note">
        <strong>Pad savers:</strong> Mirka pad savers fit between the backing pad and the sanding disc
        to protect the pad during aggressive, continuous net sanding. Change them regularly to prolong
        backing pad life.
      </div>

      <h3>Further Service</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Servicing must be performed by trained personnel. To keep the warranty valid, use a Mirka authorized service centre.</li>
        <li>Keep cooling air vents clean to ensure air circulation.</li>
        <li>Inspect the power cord regularly; replace only with an original Mirka cable (MIE9017211 for US 100&ndash;120 V).</li>
        <li>Spare parts such as the motor and speed controller are available only to authorized repairers.</li>
      </ul>

