      <h2>Troubleshooting</h2>
      <table>
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Possible Cause</th><th>Solution</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-purpose LED flashes between red and green</td>
            <td>Connected to a mains outlet with the wrong voltage</td>
            <td>Connect to an outlet matching the tool's nominal voltage (100&ndash;120 VAC)</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>No light from the Multi-purpose LED when switched on</td>
            <td>Power cord not properly attached to the tool or the mains socket</td>
            <td>Connect it properly</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-purpose LED is red and the tool slows to minimum speed while sanding</td>
            <td>Temperature too high; too heavy long-term load</td>
            <td>Reduce the load for a while and the tool will speed up again</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Multi-purpose LED is red and RPM is slightly reduced</td>
            <td>Too heavy short-term load</td>
            <td>Use a lighter load; the LED will automatically change back to green</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Brake seal does not work</td>
            <td>Worn brake seal or damaged spindle bearing</td>
            <td>Check and replace the brake seal or spindle bearing if necessary</td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Tool has stopped and the Multi-purpose LED is red</td>
            <td>Tool is in safety mode due to high temperature</td>
            <td>Wait until the tool has cooled down</td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Disposal</h2>
      <div class="warning">
        Render redundant power tools unusable by removing the power cord. Observe country-specific
        regulations regarding disposal and recycling of disused machines, packaging, and accessories.
        Do not dispose of electric power tools in household waste.
      </div>

